[sighs]

47:39.900 --> 47:40.942
[chomping]

47:40.942 --> 47:44.320
[bottle thuds]
-[sighs heavily]

47:44.320 --> 47:47.115
[footsteps scuffle]

47:47.115 --> 47:50.994
I, uh, I don't go to funerals.

47:50.994 --> 47:53.871
I can't bring myself to.
I-I skip 'em.

47:53.871 --> 47:57.500
I send mountains of flowers
and food to the wake,

47:57.500 --> 48:00.712
convince myself
that's the right thing to do.

48:00.712 --> 48:04.049
If I were asked why, I'd say,

48:04.049 --> 48:06.050
"Well, we wanna remember him
how he was,"

48:06.050 --> 48:10.513
or some other bullshit.

48:10.513 --> 48:12.307
Truth?

48:12.307 --> 48:15.059
I like to keep moving so I don't
have to think about it.

48:15.059 --> 48:16.937
More truth?

48:16.937 --> 48:19.522
I'm not the type to grapple
with it all.

48:19.522 --> 48:22.442
But...

48:22.442 --> 48:25.611
There was no way that
I was gonna skip this one.

48:28.323 --> 48:31.451
Because Donnie...

48:31.451 --> 48:33.953
grappled with all of it.

48:33.953 --> 48:37.623
He was courage.

48:37.623 --> 48:40.877
And...hope.

48:42.920 --> 48:45.048
And his intelligence
and his kindness

48:45.048 --> 48:47.968
made me wanna be
all those things, too.

48:47.968 --> 48:49.886
As it did all of you.

48:54.849 --> 48:57.935
I am so angry that he's gone.

49:01.939 --> 49:05.068
So glad that while he was here,

49:05.068 --> 49:08.321
I was one of the lucky few
who knew him.

49:12.116 --> 49:14.369
I admired Donnie Caan.

49:18.122 --> 49:20.625
And I am proud to have
called him a friend.

49:20.625 --> 49:24.087
[wind blowing, leaves rustling]

49:24.087 --> 49:26.923
[cup rustles]

49:26.923 --> 49:28.508
[footsteps scuffle]

49:28.508 --> 49:31.803
[exhales]
Let's do this. Donnie.

49:31.803 --> 49:34.639
[all] To Donnie.

49:36.391 --> 49:37.725
[sips]

49:37.725 --> 49:40.603
[Bryan] Why you working
from home today?

49:40.603 --> 49:44.482
I went to a funeral
and got kicked out...

49:44.482 --> 49:46.151
by my wife.

49:48.111 --> 49:51.989
I needed the quiet.
[sighs]

49:53.491 --> 49:54.951
The Judge Wilcox arrest...

49:54.951 --> 49:56.786
Mm-hmm?

49:56.786 --> 49:58.955
-Slick move.
-Mm.

49:58.955 --> 50:00.123
[both chuckle softly]

50:00.123 --> 50:03.418
That wasn't it. It was
just the opener, right?

50:05.170 --> 50:08.381
You got rid of an impediment,
but that's not enough.

50:08.381 --> 50:11.008
You're putting in
your own blocker.

50:11.008 --> 50:14.179
You wanna put someone
in that seat --

50:14.179 --> 50:16.180
someone who'll owe you,
not someone who's compromised.

50:16.180 --> 50:20.227
Just a more...willing ear.

50:21.769 --> 50:23.563
[chuckles]

50:23.563 --> 50:24.730
The person
needs to be qualified.

50:24.730 --> 50:27.024
He or she
needs to check out

50:27.024 --> 50:29.527
gold stars
across the board.

50:29.527 --> 50:31.196
[sighs]

50:31.196 --> 50:32.613
It's a Senate appointment,
the Judiciary committee,

50:32.613 --> 50:37.285
so it won't be immediate,
but it won't be long either.

50:37.285 --> 50:40.246
Yeah, you're almost there.

50:40.246 --> 50:41.914
Hmm.

50:44.625 --> 50:46.377
Adam DeGiulio?

50:48.421 --> 50:50.423
And then he's out of your way
at the AG's office, too.

50:50.423 --> 50:55.095
And maybe he leaves a friendly
behind in his place.

50:55.095 --> 50:56.637
Wow.

50:56.637 --> 50:59.765
Don't get too excited
by how good it sounds.

50:59.765 --> 51:03.103
Everything's gotta fall
just  right. [chuckles]

51:03.103 --> 51:04.228
And the odds
of that happening --

51:04.228 --> 51:07.064
Still, you're playing
the game again. Clear-eyed.

51:07.064 --> 51:09.817
Oh, that I am.

51:09.817 --> 51:11.360
Drink?

51:11.360 --> 51:15.281
No. I'll -- I'll keep mine
clear, too.

51:15.281 --> 51:16.991
[pats arm]

51:16.991 --> 51:20.411
[wind blowing]

51:20.411 --> 51:23.414
[birds calling in distance]

51:34.342 --> 51:36.469
You all right?

51:36.469 --> 51:38.095
Sad.

51:38.095 --> 51:40.389
Yeah. Good guy.

51:40.389 --> 51:44.186
One of the few people at work
who were remotely interesting.

51:44.186 --> 51:45.728
Tell me about it.

51:46.854 --> 51:50.316
And...he was our gay guy.

51:51.609 --> 51:53.945
That make a difference?

51:53.945 --> 51:55.738
Yeah.

51:55.738 --> 51:58.574
These days,
it's great to have a gay.

52:00.701 --> 52:03.621
You are a complete
goddamn animal.

52:07.083 --> 52:09.919
[champagne sloshes]

52:09.919 --> 52:12.004
[bottle clinks]

52:12.004 --> 52:14.048
I ruined his life.

52:15.841 --> 52:16.884
Say again?

52:16.884 --> 52:20.263
[inhales deeply]
Donnie.

52:20.263 --> 52:23.015
I was able to patch him up,

52:23.015 --> 52:26.727
keep him in a game
that made him miserable.

52:26.727 --> 52:28.229
If I just...

52:28.229 --> 52:30.731
let him fail, get fired,
he would've been better off.

52:30.731 --> 52:32.358
He could've made the life
he wanted.

52:32.358 --> 52:33.818
That's kind of
a stretch, Wendy.

52:33.818 --> 52:35.319
Oh, he would've been
so much happier

52:35.319 --> 52:37.280
if he'd returned
to academia.

52:37.280 --> 52:38.781
Give me a break.

52:38.781 --> 52:42.410
College professors are broke
as fuck and bitter, too.

52:42.410 --> 52:44.371
They certainly don't leave
40 mil to their families

52:44.371 --> 52:46.581
when they knock off.

52:46.581 --> 52:49.375
Now, what...
[sighs]

52:49.375 --> 52:54.381
is really  going on,
Dr. Rhoades?

52:54.381 --> 52:56.424
Is it a little case
of projection?

52:56.424 --> 52:58.343
[bottle clinks]

52:58.343 --> 53:01.721
Donnie walked with 40?

53:01.721 --> 53:04.307
Hyperbole.

53:04.307 --> 53:06.393
Just making my point.

53:08.311 --> 53:11.273
Right.

53:11.273 --> 53:13.941
Worst part of my job,
I'll tell you that.

53:13.941 --> 53:16.819
-Ari.
-Hey, Bobby.

53:16.819 --> 53:20.407
Thank you, Dr. Gilbert,
for the excellent care,

53:20.407 --> 53:22.242
for trying so hard.

53:27.371 --> 53:30.082
Walter, we're gonna take off.

53:30.082 --> 53:31.375
[sighs]

53:31.375 --> 53:34.211
[lowered voice] A messenger's
gonna stop by tomorrow.

53:34.211 --> 53:35.921
You'll have all the info.

53:35.921 --> 53:37.840
Any problems,
you have the number, right?

53:37.840 --> 53:39.925
Yes.

53:39.925 --> 53:41.427
Thank you.

53:41.427 --> 53:45.390
I  should be thanking  you.

53:45.390 --> 53:48.851
I took him away from you.

53:48.851 --> 53:52.897
He should've been
with his family, with you.

53:52.897 --> 53:56.401
No. You pulled him
out of a dark well,

53:56.401 --> 53:58.819
made him himself again.

53:58.819 --> 54:00.696
Got him reaching for
that final piece of life

54:00.696 --> 54:04.533
instead of watching it go.
[chuckles]

54:04.533 --> 54:05.868
[whispers] Oh, honey.

54:10.290 --> 54:12.083
It was a good send-off.

54:12.083 --> 54:14.460
[sniffles]
It was very Donnie.

54:14.460 --> 54:15.711
[all chuckle]

54:15.711 --> 54:17.963
[sniffles]

54:17.963 --> 54:20.424
So nothing to worry about
on the Secret Santa front.

54:20.424 --> 54:22.677
I really couldn't have that
around the house.

54:22.677 --> 54:25.096
Donnie loved doing it
so much. [chuckles]

54:25.096 --> 54:28.475
He kept saying, "I just
wanna make it to Christmas

54:28.475 --> 54:31.936
so I can be Santa
one more time."

54:31.936 --> 54:33.438
He'd see them get the gifts

54:33.438 --> 54:37.274
and beam straight through
New Year's.

54:38.818 --> 54:41.445
He just didn't make it.

54:47.952 --> 54:50.287
Okay. I'll meet you
in the waiting room.

54:50.287 --> 54:51.330
Okay.

54:54.291 --> 54:55.584
[door creaks closed]

54:59.130 --> 55:01.298
Ari? How is he?

55:01.298 --> 55:03.426
It's not contained,
and it's spreading quickly.

55:03.426 --> 55:06.762
I'm not into the calendar game,
but...two, three months.

55:08.431 --> 55:10.517
That's a shame.

55:10.517 --> 55:12.101
He is a candidate for
a drug trial in Pittsburgh

55:12.101 --> 55:15.229
that's been yielding some
pretty interesting results.

55:15.229 --> 55:16.605
Such as?

55:16.605 --> 55:18.691
Slowing growth down,
buying time, really.

55:18.691 --> 55:20.651
How much?

55:20.651 --> 55:25.197
Three or four months more,
six.

55:25.197 --> 55:27.367
I can get him in,

55:27.367 --> 55:30.119
but it is
a pretty rigorous course.

55:30.119 --> 55:32.329
So...kind of rough

55:32.329 --> 55:34.373
